post_text:
@DorrisIntermediateSchool students in Miss Rawls' and Mrs. Cigliana's classes treated their school to a living history lesson as they presented a Living Wax Museum featuring African American Inventors.

The museum was the culmination of a month-long Black History Month project to research and prepare a presentation about an African American inventor.

Exhibits in the museum came to life when visitors pressed an imaginary button to activate a short speech from the famous inventor. #thekahokway #proudtobeakahok

